Package tripleplay.syncdb

Interface Summary
Protocol.Server Abstracts away the sending of a sync request to the server.
Resolver<T> Provides a mechanism for resolving conflict between two conflicting values in a sync db.
SetResolver Provides a mechanism for resolving conflict between two conflicting sets in a sync db.
 

Class Summary
Codec<T> Handles encoding/decoding properties to/from strings.
Codec.EnumC<E extends Enum<E>> A codec for enums which encodes to/from Enum.name.
DBUtil SyncDB related utility methods.
Protocol Handles the process of syncing a databse with the server.
Protocol.NetServer A Protocol.Server implementation that delivers deltas to the server via Net.
Protocol.PayloadReader Used to decode ints and strings from one big compact string.
Protocol.PayloadWriter Used to encode ints and strings in one big compact string.
Protocol.Request Encapsulates a sync request from the client.
Protocol.Response Encapsualtes a response from the server.
Protocol.Session Encapsulates a syncing session with the server.
SyncDB A database of key/value pairs that is synced (via a server) across multiple devices.
